node.text:
The Everglades are truly an amazing place 🙌 but very few are explore in the dark 🌙 and that’s when you can see some crazy things 😱 Juliette and I saw some incredible animals in just a short period of time and wow am I glad to share it with you all 🙏
.
.
.

node.text:
Out of all of California I don’t think I can find a cooler ball python collection than this 🐍 Miguel @alwaysevolvingpythons has some of the most beautiful snakes I’ve ever seen 😳 and I’ve seen a thing or two 😂 so these will definitely blow you away in this epic Part 1 IGTV 📺 
.

.

node.text:
When the big reticulated pythons lay their eggs 🥚 the best thing for the babies and the mom is to remove the eggs 🤷‍♂️ this is because the babies get a higher chance at successfully hatching 🐣 and the mom gets to go back to her normal life quicker 🐍 of course mama doesn’t know I’m trying to help 😬 which can make it interesting 😂 
.
.
.

It’s time to feed the gators 🐊 and they sure do love their chicken 🍗 I like to cut it up because although they could eat the whole thing 🐓 it is good enrichment to be able to grab so many pieces 🤷‍♂️ and it’s easier on their tummies 😃 just like when mom always told you to make sure you chew your food 😂 have fun with us in this feeding frenzy IGTV 📺 
.

.

node.text:
It is so hard to decided which vipers are cooler 😆 the rhino vipers in the last unbxing video 📦 or these epic vipers 🐍 which happen to have the longest fangs of any venomous snake in the world 😱 now thats no joke 😬 I'm so happy to have them here at The Zoo to share with all the visitors 🙌 and to educate countless people in person and over the world wide web 📱 
.
.
.
